# Product rules

- Safety and trust come before growth hacks or engagement tricks.
- Prefer clarity over cleverness in flows, copy, and UI.
- Optimize for fast time-to-value after signup (meaningful match path).
- Use inclusive, respectful language; avoid cringe or pressure tactics.
- Do not use dark patterns for boosts, subscriptions, or matches.
- Every feature should support trust, retention, or meaningful matches—or question whether it belongs.
- Reduce unnecessary profile friction; keep onboarding focused on trust, profile quality, and first-match speed.
- Respect user intent; do not invent hidden product decisions—ask when requirements are unclear.

See also: `AGENTS.md`, `PROJECT_OVERVIEW.md`.
